&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Registered Mental Health Nurse &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Permanent&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 5 - 37.5 Hours/Week (part time also available)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of the trust vision to provide nationally celebrated, community focused healthcare, we are investing in the recruitment of new Registered Mental Health Nurse’s to support our current nursing establishment on Millbridge Ward and across the trust. This is a brand new role to help support patients presenting with mental health issues such as Eating Disorders, Depression, Anxiety and those detained under the Mental Health Act 1983.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for newly qualified or experienced Registered Mental Health Nurse’s to be part of our dynamic team to provide one to one support for vulnerable patients. The suitable applicants will have excellent communications skills and a caring and compassionate nature. You would be required to actively engage with the patients that require enhanced supervision through therapeutic patient activities and engagement skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate’s will be expected to deliver high standards of patient-centered care showing empathy, patience and understanding at all times. You will also play a vital role in supporting and educating junior staff or students (supervision will be provided) on how to manage patients with challenging behavior.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be given a detailed induction to the role by the Ward Manager and the Alcohol Liaison Lead (RMN) and you will be fully supported by our friendly multidisciplinary team throughout your role. You will also have opportunity to shadow with our Psychiatric Liaison Service to obtain further skills and knowledge to develop your existing skills as a RMN.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;If you require any further information, please contact:&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Medical Matron Sreeja Sukumaran on 01483 571122 ext 6870 &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Millbridge Ward Manager Bjorn Ramirez on ext 2594 &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Anthony Gartland (Alcohol Liaison Lead) on 01483 571122 ext 6623.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
